:For the sense of "sequencing" used in [[electronic music]], see the [[music
sequencer]] article. For sequence learning in cognitive science, see [[sequence
learning]].

In genetics and biochemistry, 'sequencing' means to determine the primary
structure (sometimes falsely called primary sequence) of an unbranched
biopolymer. Sequencing results in a symbolic linear depiction known as a
'sequence' which succinctly summarizes much of the atomic-level structure of the
sequenced molecule.
